<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
        .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
        .header { background-color: #FF9800; color: white; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
        .content { padding: 20px; background-color: #f9f9f9; }
        .alert-box { 
            background-color: #FFF3E0; 
            border-left: 5px solid #FF9800;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }
        .footer { text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; font-size: 0.9em; color: #777; }
        .amount { font-weight: bold; color: #F44336; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Budget Alert</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="content">
            <p>Hello <%= user.name %>,</p>
            <p>You've exceeded your budget for the following category:</p>
            
            <div class="alert-box">
                <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Budget Limit Exceeded</h3>
                <p><strong>Category:</strong> <%= category %></p>
                <p><strong>Amount Spent:</strong> <span class="amount">$<%= amount.toFixed(2) %></span></p>
                <p><strong>Budget Limit:</strong> $<%= budget.toFixed(2) %></p>
                <p><strong>Over Budget By:</strong> $<%= (amount - budget).toFixed(2) %></p>
            </div>
            
            <p>Consider reviewing your expenses in this category to stay on track with your financial goals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer">
            <p>Â© <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> Expense Tracker. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
